<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,416,222,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: With the character states of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[780,876,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,876,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the widest sense, see above), restricted or amplified as follows: small-sized species (L 
<quantity box="[659,799,258,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="6.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.2" valueMin="6.8">6.8–8.2 mm</quantity>
). Head and pronotum brownish, elytra metallic green to cupreous, without reddish patch. Apical labial palpomeres markedly securiform in both male and female. Pronotal disc heavily punctate (
<figureCitation box="[404,483,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1822,1844]" captionTargetBox="[158,1420,311,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,301,1801]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Calleida puncticollis sp. n. 22 habitus and labels of holotype (male, Hubei, IZAS), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 23 habitus of paratype (female, Shaanxi, IZAS), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 24 pronotum (Shaanxi, China), [coarsely punctate], scale bar = 0.5 mm; 25 ovipositor (Hubei, China), scale bar = 0.1 mm; 26 female reproductive tract (Hubei, China), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 27 median lobe of aedeagus, right-lateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 28 left and right parameres of aedeagus (holotype), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 29 male sternum IX (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1302721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Abdominal sternum VII not notched at apex both in males and females (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1422,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1664,1686]" captionTargetBox="[216,1350,195,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[216,1350,195,1626]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Characters of Calleida spp. 1–3 sternum VII of males: 1 C. cf. splendidula (Guangdong, China), [apex notched, one seta on each side]; 2 C. fukiensis (Fujian, China), [apex notched, two setae on each side]; 3 C. puncticollis sp. n. (Holotype, Hubei, China), [apex straight, four setae on each side]. 4–6 sternum VII of females: 4 C. cf. splendidula (Guangdong, China), [two setae on each side]; 5 C. fukiensis (Shaanxi, China), [three setae on each side]; 6 C. puncticollis sp. n. (Hubei, China), [six and seven setae on each side]. 7–9 basal three antennomeres: 7 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [with sparse additional setae]; 8 C. excelsa (Yunnan, China), [with dense additional setae]; 9 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [without additional setae]. 10 elytral shoulder, C. sultana (Yunnan, China), [humeral margins setose]. 11–14 pronotal anterior angle: 11 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [with erect setae]; 12 C. excelsa (Yunnan, China), [with erect setae]; 13 C. sultana (Yunnan, China), [with erect setae]; 14 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [without setae]. 15–18 elytral outer apical angle: 15 C. corporaali (Sabah, Malaysia), [acute, forming sharp tooth]; 16 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [markedly widened, not forming tooth]; 17 C. doriae (Yunnan, China), [slightly widened]; 18 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [completely round, not widened]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1302715/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">figs. 3, 6</figureCitation>
), with eight setae in males, ten or more setae in females. Median lobe of aedeagus stout, endophallus without any chitinized copulatory pieces (
<figureCitation box="[480,558,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1822,1844]" captionTargetBox="[158,1420,311,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,301,1801]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Calleida puncticollis sp. n. 22 habitus and labels of holotype (male, Hubei, IZAS), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 23 habitus of paratype (female, Shaanxi, IZAS), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 24 pronotum (Shaanxi, China), [coarsely punctate], scale bar = 0.5 mm; 25 ovipositor (Hubei, China), scale bar = 0.1 mm; 26 female reproductive tract (Hubei, China), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 27 median lobe of aedeagus, right-lateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 28 left and right parameres of aedeagus (holotype), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 29 male sternum IX (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1302721/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,438,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
: Only one species, 
<taxonomicName box="[612,777,438,463]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticollis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[612,777,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. puncticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[784,848,438,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[784,848,438,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, is attributed to this group. This species is very rare in collections but recorded from several provinces in central and eastern China (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1120,475,499]" captionStart="MAP 2" captionStartId="14.[151,209,1249,1271]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1227]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,195,1227]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="MAP 2 Distributions for species in the C. puncticollis group: C. puncticollis sp. n. (red)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1302723/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">map 2</figureCitation>
). The systematic position of this species group is rather isolated in the Asiatic fauna because of the peculiar characters of endophallus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The following peculiar characters isolate this group from all other known Asiatic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[1132,1229,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1132,1229,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known so far: abdominal sternum VII in male not notched, and endophallus without copulatory pieces. In all other Asiatic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[151,247,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,247,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the male anal sternum is distinctly notched, and the endophallus has distinct chitinized copulatory pieces, composed of long flagellum or two short pieces. This is also the only Asiatic species with abdominal sternum VII with more than two apical setae in males (more than four in females) not included in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller in Mindanao" authorityYear="1921" box="[1207,1436,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoidalis">
<emphasis box="[1207,1436,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Calleida discoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (see Key to the species groups), which will be treated in a separate contribution. However, the different external and male sexual characters mentioned above suggested that these two groups may not closely related at all.
</paragraph>
